snippet.textDisplay: It is absolutely criminal how over-instrumentation is overshadowing Lala's voice, taking away it's nuances, you can barely hear him. And yet still this song manages to be one of the saving graces of this season. I would have said I'd love to see more Saraiki music on Coke Studio but after the way they massacred Baazi I was apprehensive about this track but the father and son duo manage to be amazing despite the terrible production that has the become the hallmark of CS lately.
snippet.textOriginal: It is absolutely criminal how over-instrumentation is overshadowing Lala's voice, taking away it's nuances, you can barely hear him. And yet still this song manages to be one of the saving graces of this season. I would have said I'd love to see more Saraiki music on Coke Studio but after the way they massacred Baazi I was apprehensive about this track but the father and son duo manage to be amazing despite the terrible production that has the become the hallmark of CS lately.
